{{doc/start}}
Renders a styled infobox for an exploration unlock. Data is pulled automatically from [[Module:Data/ExplorationUnlocks]]. The infobox displays the unlock's title, category, unlock time, required items, prerequisite exploration unlocks, and any research required.

Pages using this template are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-pages</code>. Editors can add content below the infobox but should not modify the template call itself.

== Data source ==
Exploration unlock data comes from [[Module:Data/ExplorationUnlocks]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit data modules directly.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Infobox Exploration Unlock|id=_base_eu_iron_ore}}
{{Infobox Exploration Unlock|id=_base_eu_iron_ore|image=Iron Ore.png}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> || Exploration unlock template identifier from the game data (e.g. <code>_base_eu_iron_ore</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>image</code> || Image filename to display. The module prepends <code>Item_</code> automatically. Exploration unlock images are typically stored as <code>File:Item_NAME (Exploration).png</code>. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* Prerequisite exploration unlocks link to <code>NAME (Exploration Unlock)</code> pages.
* The category label is derived from the <code>category_id</code> field by stripping the <code>_base_</code> prefix and title-casing the result.
* The infobox automatically adds <code>[[Category:Exploration Unlocks]]</code>.
{{doc/end}}
